subject: Last call for QS-ASCII proposals

messageBody:
This list has been quiet recently. I'd like to remind everyone that as
January draws to a close, we're ready to start voting to determine a
standard set of ASCII letter assignments for QS. The proposals have
been discussed at length already. You can review them in the document
'qs_keybd_proposals3.csv' in the Files->Key mapping proposals
directory on the group website. Benct and I have made subdirectories
there with files that explain our proposals. Peter and Moira have
explained their proposals in email. I will also collect the text
examples using each mapping that we've compared over email, and update
them to the latest versions of the proposals and put them in a
document in that directory.

It's not too late to submit a new proposal! If after reviewing the
proposals listed in 'qs_keybd_proposals3.csv' you find them all
lacking, send me another proposal and I'll add it to the list.

Thanks.

Ted
